#--: IDEA: error not to store reftypes returned

If a function returns a reftype, it should be an error to not store or
otherwise use (eg. by immediately calling a method on it) that reftype.

Reftypes take work to allocate on the heap and build... it is likely an error
not to use it at the call site. Or is a job for linter?

